{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-blog-post-tsx","path":"/blocks-layout-elements","result":{"data":{"post":{"author":{"node":{"firstName":"Tyler","lastName":"Barnes","name":"tylbar","uri":"/author/tyler/","avatar":{"url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/0a5bd2d18281009a03f01b8378abada1?s=96&d=mm&r=g"}}},"id":"cG9zdDoxNzM0","excerpt":"<p>The columns: Column two. Column three. Column four. Media &amp;Text For displaying media and text next to each other. By default, the media is to the left. This time our block is full width, and the image is to the right. The background color is a pale blue.&nbsp; Test to make sure that the editor [&hellip;]</p>\n","content":"\n<div class=\"wp-block-group has-background\" style=\"background-color:#d8f6ec\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<p>The Layout Elements category includes the following blocks: <em>Group, Button, Columns, Media &amp; Text, separator, spacer, read more, and page break.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<p>This group block has a light green background color.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-button\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link\">A button</a></div>\n\n\n\n<p>The read more block should be right below this text, but only on list pages of themes that show the full content. It won&#8217;t show on the single page or on themes showing excerpts.</p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<!--more-->\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns has-4-columns\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\">\n<p>The columns:</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\">\n<p>Column two.</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\">\n<p>Column three.</p>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\">\n<p>Column four.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text alignwide\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><span class=\"wp-image-757 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%;width:1600px\" data-reactroot=\"\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\